~

Bunk Hotel Utrecht 🌿
~
While we were in Utrecht we stayed in this awesome hotel called BUNK. The hotel is as converted church, has lighting in the bedroom that changes colour and the food was really lovely in their restaurant. Really easy to check in to and the staff are all friendly. Would recommend to everyone! ~

Kayaking through Utrecht 🛶
~
On the third day of our trip, we hired kayaks from Canoe Rental Utrecht. This was a really unique way to see the city and were really cheap to hire! Make sure you follow the map tho as we took a wrong turning and ended up kayaking for 4 hours 🙄😂
~

Kinderdijk, a village in Netherlands’ south Holland providence, was one of the prettiest places we’ve visited, known for its iconic 18th-century windmills 🌿🇳🇱
~
Follow @gallivantingtogether for more travel inspiration!
~
#windmills #windmilll #kinderdijk #kinderdijkmills #kinderdijk🇳🇱 #kinderdijkwindmills #kinderdijkphotography #netherlands🇳🇱 #bridgeview #europe_greatshots #europe_ig #europe #travel #traveling #tourism #tourtheplanet #scenery #scenic #travelling #motorbiketravel #nature #nature_captures #holland #holland🇳🇱 #holland_photos #hollanda #holland_photolovers #visitnetherlands #visitholland #thisisholland

On the second day of our trip to the Netherlands, we rode to Kinderdijk to see all the windmills there. We had a lovely walk around and they have a few museums about how the windmills work etc. One of the museums is in a windmill too! Definitely worth a visit.
~
For those who ride motorbikes: I’m wearing my @bull_itjeans jeans and @formaboots for safety. They are super comfy!
~

Be there or be square 🔶
.
Day 1 in the Netherlands: if you’re in Rotterdam you’ve got to go and see all the amazing architecture! Especially the Cube House by Piet Blom. You can get pictures from so many angles. We spent a good hour looking around it all. .
.
